ely case studies, they define peer coaching as a focused relationship between equals who supportively learn from, actively listen to, and judiciously question each other, which leads to breakthroughs that may otherwise lie dormant in one's career. A fundamental guide for anyone with an interest in mentoring and transformational learning, this book is a must-have for the talent management bookshelf.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCareer development. 0aEmployeesxCoaching of. 0aPersonnel management. 4aVUCA. 4acoordinated management of meaning. 4adeep learning. 4alearning culture. 4apeer coaching groups. 4apeer coaching. 4arelational learning. 4arisk factors. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Careers / General.2bisacsh1 aHall, Douglas T. (Tim), eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKram, Kathy E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360506040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503605060423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503605060.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles